25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=471.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What a mistake is......</span><hr size=1> Since I can't edit it out... Your point was not that it was premeditated.. that was someone else in another post using the same analogy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Showing TOTAL disregard for other people, their rights, and feelings.<br>
<br>
Doing what you feel to someone because you're bigger and stronger than them.<br>
<br>
These things are....... lets just call them BAD THINGS.<br>
<br>
When someone makes a mistake they say OOPS!<br>
<br>
When someone does a BAD THING they say MUAHAHAHAHA<br>
<br>
When someone does a BAD THING to apologize for making a MISTAKE is insincere at best, arrongant and evil at worst.&quot;<br>
<br>
All of these are errors in judgement. That is the very core of what a mistake is. Don't get me wrong.. saying something is a mistake does NOT reduce the accountability for what has been done, it merely is an admittance of a past wrong.<br>
<br>
To say something was not a mistake because of the intentions behind it is completely ignoring the very nature of what a mistake is. These intentions are formulated through an error in judgement.<br>
<br>
When someone commits and accident they say &quot;OOPS!,&quot; when someone commits a mistake they say &quot;I'm sorry.&quot; &quot;OOPS&quot; signifies that the action was not premeditated and it was not done on purpose.. thus an accident.<br>
<br>
